website_summaries.verdict: A very sturdy hardshell case with quality features to protect your acoustic guitar.
pros: A sturdy wooden case that is still reasonably lightweight
Very plush on the inside with a larger headstock area that will fit 6- and 12-string acoustics
Metal feet on the bottom and sides protect the case on the outside
cons: More expensive than a soft case and doesn't include any additional storage

customer_reviews.title: Good but... not 4.5" deep.
customer_reviews.text: Beware: the description says Internal dimension Height 4.5" . That is not true in this case. (pun intended). It is barely 4". Other dimensions are correct. If your guitar is deeper than 4" this case will squash it a bit. The pictures show an item that is 4.5 inches and what happens when it's placed in the case and the top is closed. When they measured the internal depth, they were not too careful...I hope this helps them fix the description. I'm still looking for a case to fit my 1856 Torres model.
customer_reviews.author: wholegoose

customer_reviews.title: Great 3/4 guitar case!
customer_reviews.text: Nicely made, very secure, very plush on the inside. And a bit heavy, but it keeps the guitar safe from my klutzy self. I originally ordered this case for my Luna Safari Muse Nylon guitar; it's a bit roomy for the Luna but a little bit of padding on the bout end of the case makes the Safari more secure. I bought a Cordoba Cadete 3/4 guitar shortly after ordering the case, and the Cadete fits like the case was made for it - no movement at all in the case.
customer_reviews.author: Kindle CustomerTop Contributor: Guitars

customer_reviews.title: Great protective hard case!
customer_reviews.text: This is a great guitar case! I purchased this case b/c my daughter started taking a guitar class after school & I wanted her guitar to be better protected than it was in the lightweight fabric backpack case her guitar came with. This case totally lives up to expectations- it’s sturdy and nicely made. It has four latches to keep it securely closed & one latch has a locking feature. My daughter’s Ibanez junior fits perfectly inside. I would definitely recommend this case.
customer_reviews.author: JSkor

customer_reviews.title: NOT an archtop case- flat.
customer_reviews.text: Case that showed up was NOT like the photo. Photo shows a very clear arched top. Case that arrived is flat-topped. It's not a BAD case, it's just not an arch-top case as shows in ALL the product photos online. You can push the top on this one down with some effort and an arch-top case would be much sturdier. I might return it.
customer_reviews.author: NMHighPlains

customer_reviews.title: Fits like a glove.
customer_reviews.text: Better than I expected! Fits the Gretsch Jim Dandy Parlor guitar like a glove. This is the case you are looking for if you own one of these guitars! We all know gig bags just don't cut it. I bought this guitar to travel with and again this is the case you're looking for. Very well made and very light weight for a wooden case which makes lugging it through an airport much easier. Has extra padding at the base. Has feet both on the sides and on the bottom to protect the case from scuffs. The storage compartment has plenty of space for straps, picks, electric tuners, etc.
customer_reviews.author: slamming96

customer_reviews.title: OVERATED
customer_reviews.text: Although sturdy, the outside of the case is a disappointment. It looks like cardboard, and I suspect it wouldn't take much to mar it. But the inside is surprisingly very nice. We'll see how it does over time. My experience has been that companies are putting out more and more inferior products but charging more for them. It's too bad.
customer_reviews.author: Pam

customer_reviews.title: A perfect "after-market" case."
customer_reviews.text: It may not be as good as the case you got with your Gibson or Guild, but it is strong, it can take considerable abuse without even scuffing, the latches are adequate if not the best, and the plush lining seems just right to make it fit about any standard guitar as long as the guitar is not a jumbo. And the price sure is friendly!
customer_reviews.author: Baumli

customer_reviews.title: Great fitting case for Larrivee Parlor Guitar.
customer_reviews.text: Careful with the one catch on the back side of the case. (hinge side). This fits my Larrivee Parlor like a glove. However, if you open the case and don't open that back hatch, the back hatch gets bent and becomes essentially useless. Case still works though, good enough for my storage purposes but probably not good enough for travel now.
customer_reviews.author: mdisher

customer_reviews.title: Simon and Patrick Woodland Pro Parlor Guitar works Fine with this case.
customer_reviews.text: Decided that this nice guitar needed more protection than a cheap gig bag. The case seems quite sturdy. Surprise latch on the hinge side of the case should help things stay secure. Nice plush interior, no bad smells! The S&P Parlor was pretty close to the dimensions advertised for this case and indeed they seem spot on. This was a deliver next day item from Amazon , and that worked out just fine. Amazon packing was not great, the case was just rattling around in a much bigger box without any packing, but there was no damage other than the bottom of the plastic bag holding the case was a bit torn. Best of luck to all Lee in Florida
customer_reviews.author: Lee Copp

customer_reviews.title: Perfect fit for Fender 12 string guitar-quality Gator case
customer_reviews.text: Bought this to hold my Fender 12 string guitar. (12 strings can have longer necks) The “Gator Brand “ 6/12 string case was a perfect fit! Great price too! Arrived 1 day earlier than expected. Zero damage to box or case. Thanks UPS! There’s a compartment inside to hold stuff-picks, cleaning cloth, tuner, etc. VERY sturdy. Black “fur” with cushioning. Lock buckles feel substantial & sturdy-not cheap. Pretty lightweight as far as guitar cases go. I’m VERY happy with this purchase & feel my 12 string will be secure in this case. Quality product!
customer_reviews.author: E.M. 3

customer_reviews.title: It no longer fits the Jim Dandy well.
customer_reviews.text: The case received is the correct model number but it doesn't have the slight arched top pictured in Amazon's photo or on Gator's website. It seems that Gator switched to a totally flat top without even a small bump to protect the bridge. I bought it for my Jim Dandy which is the guitar pictured in the photo, but with the flat top you need to close the lid with some force putting pressure on the bridge and the top of the guitar.
customer_reviews.author: Dylan

customer_reviews.title: Great case for vintage parlor guitars!
customer_reviews.text: This is the third one of these great cases I have purchased! I've been using them for guitars I have restored that happen to be older vintage parlor guitars! The cases are very well built, sturdy latches, nice amount of padding, and hold my 19th and early 20th century parlor guitars perfectly and safely! I've got a 1925 Washburn, 1890s seven string russian Zimmermman, (shown in photo), and soon to finish another Zimmermann Brazilian rosewood parlor seven string parlor guitar. Love these Gator cases!
customer_reviews.author: yawnny

customer_reviews.title: Strong case but the outer cover is peeling off :(
customer_reviews.text: Initially I loved this case. Bought it for my 12 year old to take his classical guitar in for school. The case seemed very sturdy and well made however, after 3 months use it is starting to fall apart. The black outer covering is peeling in several areas. While I can repair this with glue, cosmetically it doesn't look nice. Overall the case is very sturdy but i'm disappointed in how the black is peeling away. Has it done it's job in protecting his guitar? Absolutely, just wish it was made better around the edges.
customer_reviews.author: Kimberly V.

customer_reviews.title: Fits like a glove.
customer_reviews.text: I bought this case for my Fender CD60SCE 12-String, and it fits perfectly. I was a little concerned because I couldn't find a review specific to my guitar. Top-notch construction inside and out, nice storage compartment. Quality clamps. And it arrived one day earlier than expected.
customer_reviews.author: Charlie Brown Head

customer_reviews.title: Good product, great value
customer_reviews.text: I bought this case for my new 7/8 classical guitar and it is almost a perfect fit. That being said, someone with a full size guitar should carefully check the dimensions to ensure a proper fit. It appears to be well made although it is somewhat heavy (but that is not a problem for me). I have not yet been able to assess how well it will hold up to airline baggage handling but I am reasonably sure that it will be fine. I cannot imagine that a better guitar case could be bought for less money.
customer_reviews.author: Scott

customer_reviews.title: Solidly made dread case
customer_reviews.text: Well-made three-ply case with a rather smelly plush lining. Fits my unusually large and oddly-shaped (half-dread, half-jumbo) 12-string guitar. Came sloppily packaged but on time. Good cover fit, solid latches. Best price around. Congrats to Amazon for displaying all interior and exterior measurements accurately.
customer_reviews.author: Darwin T.

customer_reviews.title: Protects well and looks nice
customer_reviews.text: Bought this as a case for my daughters black rogue acoustic as she is transporting it to perform these days. Fit perfectly. She loves that it locks to keep curious hands away when she isn't looking. Looks nice, has been bounced around quite a bit but protects well. Inner storage compartment holds most of her guitar stuff (picks, clamp, cloth....). Has held up perfectly, the "stitching" looks nice and she loves this case.
customer_reviews.author: Çlmc

customer_reviews.title: Looks Great, Poorly Manufactured
customer_reviews.text: It looked really good, weight was light, seemed sturdy. But literally the first time I went to latch it the entire latch just effortlessly came off the body. If the hardware was just slightly better made and attached properly it would have been nice.
customer_reviews.author: Gabriel384

customer_reviews.title: As advertised and about what you'd expect considering the price ...
customer_reviews.text: As advertised and about what you'd expect considering the price. I bought for a Santa Cruz 1929 model 00 12 fret guitar and it did fit although just a little bit on the loose side. The guitar shifts maybe a half inch but should provide plenty of protection to the guitar. If I was going to ship the guitar in this case I would add a little extra padding inside the case on either side of the upper bouts.
customer_reviews.author: S. Martin

customer_reviews.title: Worth it!
customer_reviews.text: I am overall pleased with this guitar case which I bought for my Taylor. It is very sturdy and the price was quite reasonable. The only reason I am giving it a 4 instead of a 5 is because not long after I started using it a small, wrinkled nick appeared on the outer shell, no doubt from inadvertently banging into something. That said, I would buy it again. My guitar fits snugly, no shifting around, and there is a small storage space with a flap for pics and capos.
customer_reviews.author: Amy H.

customer_reviews.title: Great  case, and inexpensive
customer_reviews.text: This case came, as others have said, with only a plastic bag around it. I was nervous about ordering it because I didn't want it to get damaged and have to return it. It came without damage, and it's just what my 68 Yamaha FG-150 needed. Fits perfectly, no issues whatsoever. I think you can get Amazon to put a box on it at checkout. I just ordered a 2nd one for another guitar I have.
customer_reviews.author: Johnny Guitar

customer_reviews.title: Great case and very sturdy!
customer_reviews.text: I had to evacuate Rockport last week due to hurricane Harvey. I grabbed my guitar, my two dogs and my cowboy boots. I've been on the go since last week staying in four different locations. This case is a little beat up, but it's serving it's purpose and protecting my Martin. I would definitely purchase it again.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: I am jumping with joy for my Gator hard shell guitar case
customer_reviews.text: I am jumping with joy for my Gator hard shell guitar case. its well made, the inside padding is perfect & best of all it fits my Martin 00018 guitar perfectly. could not be happier. service & delivery of the case was perfect. don lee
customer_reviews.author: dl

customer_reviews.title: Great Case - A Bit Heavy
customer_reviews.text: EXCELLENT case. I have this one in a tenor ukulele size and just bought this one for my Gretsch parlor guitar (Jim Dandy) and it fits like a glove. It’s a very sturdy case and made from wood rather than cardboard like many lower end/budget friendly hard cases. Being made from wood makes it notable more heavy but it’s not unmanageable by any means. I recommend this and all of the Gator cases of this style.
customer_reviews.author: Sylvie Zumwalt

customer_reviews.title: Perfect
customer_reviews.text: My late great uncle was a music teacher and he had this little Harmony parlor guitar for which I bought this case. It fits perfectly inside. Very nice quality. It will help preserve this little antique guitar.
customer_reviews.author: ElizabethAInNYS

customer_reviews.title: All-Round Excellent guitar Case
customer_reviews.text: Very, very nice case for the money. I bought this for my Vintage Yamaha FG 260 12-string & it fit perfectly. It has a good sized neck compartment to carry my strings, picks & capo and room for a good strap. I would definitely buy another case from this vendor. Excellent product, great price & FAST shipping. EXCELLENT vendor A+++++ .
customer_reviews.author: Robert Hickey

customer_reviews.title: Nice Case
customer_reviews.text: I got this case for a Triple O guitar I built from a kit from CF Martin. Perfect fit. Only criticism I have is that the lid and case body require a little push to close properly. Slight misalignment. It's not bad, but it's not perfect either.
customer_reviews.author: JHB

customer_reviews.title: Happy with the quality
customer_reviews.text: Have only had it a couple months but it seems sturdy and I think it will last a long time. It is not the lightest case, but I was looking for something to really protect my instrument. It does a good job of keeping my guitar at a stable humidity despite the fact that we heat our house with a wood stove (when I use a gel-type instrument humidifier).
customer_reviews.author: talus.rock

customer_reviews.title: Perfect for my new Cordoba Cadete
customer_reviews.text: I bought this Gator hard case to protect a new Cordoba Cadete 3/4 size guitar. I don't believe in gigbags any more since I snapped a guitar in half putting it in the trunk of the car. This fits perfectly and I'm very happy with it. It has a 4th snap in the back, much like more expensive cases. I expect many years of use from it.
customer_reviews.author: Courtney

customer_reviews.title: Fits mini Martin LX guitars.... Loosely....
customer_reviews.text: Very nice case! Make sure that you unlatch the back latch on the case before opening. I thought it was just tight until it popped open. It didn't break, but I did open it real slow. Overall, well worth the money.... Looks nice.... I'm sure it will protect my guitar better than the soft padded case that came with it. Very good buy!
customer_reviews.author: David and Chrystal

customer_reviews.title: Great bang for the buck
customer_reviews.text: As expected the handle linkage will be the weak link (hence only 4 stars), but I'm prepared to deal with that when it fails by installing an aftermarket luggage handle that will hold up. The life time warranty is great, but using that to replace that handle with a duplicate, equally fragile, handle is inefficient. However, the rich, beautiful plush interior, the rididity of the box, and the perfect fit for a classic or flamenco guitar (i.e. the Lucero LFB250Sce flamenco guitar this was purchased for) that it is advertized to be easily makes up for that. All of those things -plush interior, rigid box, good fit- mean it will, in fact, protect the instrument. Plus it just looks great.
customer_reviews.author: Weezer

customer_reviews.title: Great value, great case.
customer_reviews.text: I have spent 10X as much for a guitar case, no need really, if you don't travel then this is totally perfect. It's a guitar case that is perfectly fine, doesn't smell like many inexpensive cases, fits perfect and does it's job. It's price is utterly ridiculous when you are a prime member. Great case.
customer_reviews.author: John harrington

customer_reviews.title: Poor packaging
customer_reviews.text: Packaging was pretty minimal.. not an actual amazon box with the air bag padding. This box was huge with flimsy tape barely closing the box and the only protection was contact paper and a clear plastic bag around the actual case.. so the case was just bouncing around assuming that’s why I lost one of the pegs that belongs near the head of the case.. As for the case it fits my acoustic no problems there and it feels like great quality for the price range. Great first hard shell case to travel with.
customer_reviews.author: TEAM MC

customer_reviews.title: Awesome case!!!
customer_reviews.text: This guitar case is sturdy and great quality. The inside is really nice, plush. And, it fit my guitar like a glove, seriously! I had to search to make sure I had the exact model to fit my guitar, but once I did that, it fits perfectly! Love this case!
customer_reviews.author: NCisBeautiful

customer_reviews.title: The Perfect Case
customer_reviews.text: I’m heading off to college, and I wanted a sturdy case to fly with my guitar. I own a 3/4 Maestro by Gibson acoustic, and this fit perfectly!!! I had to remove my tail-end strap peg to get the edge of the guitar in, but it fits like heaven and I’m so confident about its safety now!! The case is so lightweight too, because I was afraid of lugging a heavy case through the airport. I’ll put in some padding around the tuners just for my doubts, but I KNOW the guitar doesn’t even have room to move around! DEFINITELY worth the money, and was cheaper than a store bought case. I’m so happy!!
customer_reviews.author: Trissha Sivalingam

customer_reviews.title: Warning: Cancer and Reproductive Harm
customer_reviews.text: At first, I was really happy with the case (the dimensions were great for my guitar, the latches were smooth, etc.), but I was unpleasantly surprised by this small disclaimer attached to the handle of the case. It's just a warning, but the website listed on the disclaimer says that these disclaimers are placed on items that have enough of one or more (wish I could italicize "or more") chemical substances that can possibly cause cancer or reproductive harm. Unfortunately, the sellers probably don't have to add this disclaimer to the product description on Amazon since it seems only California mandates it. Please be advised.
customer_reviews.author: Joseph

customer_reviews.title: Poor quality control in case and shipping
customer_reviews.text: Ordered twice and both times this nice guitar case came in a box with no packaging besides a plastic bag and empty large box. Opened to find seams on both split and wooden box split as well. Combo or because of quality of case plus poor shipment? I don’t know. Case itself overall is what we wanted but quality control is not upheld in workmanship or shipping. Disappointed daughter as it was supposed to be her bday gift gift. Reviewed a lot of these before paying $15-20 more for this one as it looked sturdiest. Back to the drawing board.
customer_reviews.author: Jennifer Novakoski

customer_reviews.title: Perfect fit, durable, lightweight and light on the wallet
customer_reviews.text: Great hard shell case at an affordable price. After comparing the inside dimensions from Gator's website to my guitar's dimensions, I was fairly confident this would fit nicely. It did not disappoint....perfect fit for my new Washburn R45RCE Resonator w/ cutaway. My guitars dimensions are: Lower bout - 14 3/8", Upper bout -10.5", Body depth - 3.75", Body length - 19.5", Overall Length - 39". This case is lightweight, which is nice because the resonator is pretty heavy. It gives better protection than a padded gig bag, is lockable and seems well made. I'm very pleased with the price, which is about $25 less than the Washburn case made for the guitar.
customer_reviews.author: S. Gilbert

customer_reviews.title: Solid and well built case
customer_reviews.text: Fits the 1/2 scale acoustic guitar I have. I had SUCH a hard time getting a hard shell case for my Ovation mini. Sturdy case : YES Value: Absolutely Light Weight: Not really .... but there WILL be weight if you want sturdiness, fool!
customer_reviews.author: Droid

customer_reviews.title: Great gator case!
customer_reviews.text: I purchased this case for our daughter and she absolutely loves it! Fast service, great product!
customer_reviews.author: Wendy M. Stumbaugh

customer_reviews.title: Poorly manufactured handle mounting
customer_reviews.text: Handle was broke on arrival... the way the handle is mounted to the body is very poor and cheap. The position the handle is mounted puts too much tension on the holding pins and caused the case to crack resulting in the handle coming off. For the money I would expect much better craftsmanship. Other than that it was very nice and I would have liked it. Sent it back for a refund
customer_reviews.author: Jeremy patty

customer_reviews.title: 3rd guitar case that arrived damaged!!
customer_reviews.text: Arrived damaged! Heard the box hit the concrete on my front porch. Sounded like the UPS man threw the box. This is 3rd guitar case that has arrived damaged! This is Christmas Eve. My last chance for a gift for my 8 year old Godson.
customer_reviews.author: sin.......s

customer_reviews.title: Great quality; super heavy
customer_reviews.text: This case is shockingly heavy. It is definitely sturdy. Our Breedlove Organic Collection Signature Concert Acoustic-Electric Guitar fits perfectly inside. I would recommend this case, despite how heavy it is.
customer_reviews.author: JR

customer_reviews.title: I think this is a great case for the money.
customer_reviews.text: I wanted something more sturdy for when we travel than the soft case that came with my Taylor 214CE. This did the trick and fits the 214CE very well. Only for occasional travel so I didn't see the need to spend $200 on a Taylor case.
customer_reviews.author: Joseph M Marchetti

customer_reviews.title: The fit is perfect.
customer_reviews.text: First off, Gator cases are one of the two best makers on the market. SKB is top dog, but, the price reflects it. This case fits like a glove. My guitar will be safe in this 000 case, no doubt.
customer_reviews.author: Mickey Maguire

customer_reviews.title: Guitars won't Fit
customer_reviews.text: None of my acustic guitars will fit in this case, it is too shallow. I purchased it for the Martin Johnny Cash Guitar I just bought. Guitar missing the end pin and guitar will not fit in case. I am not a happy camper!
customer_reviews.author: Thomas

customer_reviews.title: Came with a broken closure and leather not glued down...
customer_reviews.text: Good case but it came with a broken closure and the leather was coming up in an area... They gave me a discount on it so it was fine, but kind of annoying they would ship something less than perfect.
customer_reviews.author: Lo

customer_reviews.title: very well built, interior padding is excellent
customer_reviews.text: Purchased for my Yamaha 12-string. This fits perfectly. I was skeptical given the price difference between this and the next lowest case, but it is fantastic. I will buy other cases from this company.
customer_reviews.author: Ross

customer_reviews.title: Short term solution.
customer_reviews.text: Mediocre and loose fit. I would not rely on this other than commuting to and from the neighbors house. Arrived with dings and had a few busted seams. Being that I am too lazy to return it, I’d rather have spent more on a case and got something that would last for 10 years. This is a 3-4 year case at the most.
customer_reviews.author: Rob V2

customer_reviews.title: Will not fit a Martin 0-18
customer_reviews.text: I really like gator cases, I have a couple and they're very sturdy and perfect if you don't need to take them on a plane but just store or do local travel with your instrument. I'm giving this 3 stars because there was nothing wrong with the case or the delivery but the case was just a little too small for my Martin 0-18. So if anyone else out there was considering this case for that guitar, look elsewhere.
customer_reviews.author: Cristian Bayer

customer_reviews.title: Gator Guitar Case- Durable!
customer_reviews.text: Since most airlines are now becoming stingy with what you can carry on board I needed a sturdy guitar travel case and this Gator Case is it. It is well made and durable and survived a few bumps and kicks on my trip with absolutely no damage to my guitar. I wasn't worried about checking the guitar in this case and so far after 4 months no issues. Would highly recommend this case for travel and/or everyday use since the price is better than the cheap cardboard ones they sell in some music stores.
customer_reviews.author: Metallicamuse- K. Casas

customer_reviews.title: A solid case and great value. This fits my Yamaha FG700S snugly/perfectly
customer_reviews.text: A solid case and great value. This fits my Yamaha FG700S snugly/perfectly. The construction appears durable and the latches seem to close securely. My guitar has taken some damage from traveling as carry-on in a gig bag and this will be a huge upgrade!
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: great for travel
customer_reviews.text: This works great as a travel case. My husband had no problems taking it to San Francisco. It's sturdy and holds the guitar perfectly in place and in tune
customer_reviews.author: Sem

customer_reviews.title: This is a very nice case, especially for the money and much nicer ...
customer_reviews.text: This is a very nice case, especially for the money and much nicer than the "budget" hard cases I've purchased from the big box music stores. It fits my Martin 000X1AE perfectly. It is properly snug just like the MARTIN case that came with my 000-15SM, and has no strong glue odor, etc. My case shipped from GearNuts, was packed very carefully, and arrived in 5 days. Very satisfied with this Gator case and the purchase experience through Amazon.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: It's the case I needed (or wanted) for the Cordoba Requinto 580
customer_reviews.text: This is a 3/4-size case. It does fit the Cordoba C5 1/2-size, which is called the Requinto 580. (I get the impression 1/2-size cases are too small for the C5 1/2-size. Anyway, it fits the Requinto 580.) The body of the guitar is snug in the case, and I do believe the guitar's top protrudes about 0.5" above the rim of the case. Since the case is padded, I do not get the notion that shutting the case compresses the guitar appreciably. That is, the particular "1/2-size" guitar I mentioned fits, not to worry.
customer_reviews.author: Raj

customer_reviews.title: Great price, nice case
customer_reviews.text: This was a gift and worked out well for both a Yamaha and an older Washburn that my son wanted to be sure and "baby" as he loves that thing. It's well padded, seemingly durable and a great price.
customer_reviews.author: T. Kirkland

customer_reviews.title: Not a tight fit for my dreadnought
customer_reviews.text: The interior of this case too large for my Blueridge BR-240a Dreadnought. It leaves a lot of room for the guitar to shift. In order to use when transporting, I have to add additional padding to keep it from banging around inside. I ended up moving my cheap Yamaha into this case, and putting my Blueridge into the Yamaha AG1-HC hard case, which has a nice snug and secure fit.
customer_reviews.author: Scot

customer_reviews.title: Lightweight & Solid Case
customer_reviews.text: Purchased this case to house an Acoustic Dreadnought Guitar that I recently finish building. Guitar fits perfectly. This is a very lightweight but solid case. I am sure that I will get many years of use out of it. For the price, this is a no brainer IMO.....
customer_reviews.author: Dr. Steven L. DC

customer_reviews.title: Great case for the money, high end low price
customer_reviews.text: Really impressed for what I paid for it. Solid case nice interior well made. I have several more expensive cases that are same quality. Have since ordered a second one.
customer_reviews.author: James Hayes

customer_reviews.title: Excellent case for $70
customer_reviews.text: Ordered this for a trip across the state, knowing it'd be in the bed of my truck without my tonneau cover on. It did the job perfectly. Even travelled to several houses during the trip without any issues. Very soft interior with a good size storage compartment. All metal brackets and hinges. The latch/ring have small tabs on the rounded head to keep the latch in place, and not slip off like some may.
customer_reviews.author: JV

customer_reviews.title: Sloppy
customer_reviews.text: Disappointed. The top doesn't close properly without having to twist it with force. The internal compartment door is loose and hardly attached. There's quite a bit of glue smeared on the fabric inside the guitar. It's better than nothing but I won't buy another Gator case.
customer_reviews.author: solmadness

customer_reviews.title: Quality Control Issues
customer_reviews.text: I placed a guitar in the case. It had not been moved since and today I find the latch laying on the floor. It seems as though this latch was not properly fastened to the case as seen in the photo.
customer_reviews.author: Calnetwork

customer_reviews.title: Very bad quality guitar case
customer_reviews.text: Quality of this guitar case is very bad. I have ordered one for my son, but received one with dents and scratches on the pvc cover. I have requested for replacement, then received second one with similar kind of scratches. Again ordered replacement for the 3rd time, received one with internal velvet padding/lining is not done properly glued. Padding edges are coming out with glue being seen out. Unhappy with product and quality check. I think there is terribly wrong with the quality check and product quality.
customer_reviews.author: Lenny

customer_reviews.title: Really nice case, but ...
customer_reviews.text: My fault. I had to return it despite being exactly what I wanted. My new Takamine 12-string was too big to fit. I should have gone by measurements, not the inclusion of the brand name in the description.
customer_reviews.author: hex-acting pro

customer_reviews.title: Good sturdy case
customer_reviews.text: Have been using for several months. Good quality, protects the guitar well. Not lightweight but it’s a hard case so of course it has some weight to it.
customer_reviews.author: Zippity_duda

customer_reviews.title: Had several bad quality cases sent
customer_reviews.text: Had several bad quality cases sent. First was torn, second had a clasp that was falling off. I just repaired the second instead of sending back, but was a pain to get two that weren't great.
customer_reviews.author: Brian G.

customer_reviews.title: Awesome Guitar Case
customer_reviews.text: Love this guitar case it's just the right size for my 1969 Brazilian Acoustic Guitar. Fit is great and excellent quality. I followed the measurements they listed and it fits like a glove.
customer_reviews.author: BUmom10

customer_reviews.title: Gator Case top notch
customer_reviews.text: Much better than what was expected. Plenty of room for accessories. You can’t go wrong for protecting your instrument.
customer_reviews.author: Clyde Sanford

customer_reviews.title: Perfect
customer_reviews.text: I bought this used and am extremely happy with the purchase. Fits both of my acoustics perfectly and all my additional strings and hardware fit well in the additional compartments. The case is extremely sturdy too!
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Works, but gets dinged up easily.
customer_reviews.text: It holds a guitar, duh, but it does not take bumps well at all. It’s only been a few months and the tolex is already coming off at some parts. It’s still structurally sound, but I worry over how this thing’s gonna hold over the course of many more months.
customer_reviews.author: Veep

customer_reviews.title: Came in broken
customer_reviews.text: Everything about the case was perfect out the box, until I inspected it well and found some damage on it. Also, when I opened it up, on the soft fluffy stuff, I could see marks of a guitar's strings imprinted on it. Giving me the idea that this was somewhat used or something.
customer_reviews.author: Roberto Delgado

customer_reviews.title: Bad Latches
customer_reviews.text: The case and the lining are good. The latches are not. The screws holding them on the case broke the third week we used it. They don’t screw back in, either, so it appears to be a defect rather than loose screws.
customer_reviews.author: DCS

customer_reviews.title: Tight fit for my Breedlove concert sized guitar but awesome case.
customer_reviews.text: This is a great case, especially for the money. The initial fit is tight for my Breedlove concert size guitar but I’m confident it will conform a bit over time. Very impressed!
customer_reviews.author: S.R.D.

customer_reviews.title: A new home for my Martin OM 1GT
customer_reviews.text: The case fits my Martin OM 1GT perfectly. The old case (not the original) gave the guitar too much room to move around. I am really pleased with this purchase.
customer_reviews.author: Bill F

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy and great looking case - fits Martin 000
customer_reviews.text: Used for Martin 000 cutaway. Fits like a glove. Looks super pro. Very pleased with the case. My only qualm is when you close the lid it doesn’t quite close all the way so it’s latchable. You have to force the lip over the side of the case before you can latch the front latches. Not a huge deal but kind of annoying. Otherwise this case is superb.
customer_reviews.author: rdlance95

customer_reviews.title: Great case.
customer_reviews.text: This case is as good as any costing much more. I build 000 size acoustic guitars and the fit and protection is great.
customer_reviews.author: Steven F. White

customer_reviews.title: Fits my Martin 000-15M Nicely
customer_reviews.text: My Martin 000-15M came with a cheap gig bag. The guitar is wonderful; the bag is a joke... This Gator case fits the guitar like a well-fitting glove. Nice case and much less expensive than a Martin hard shell case...
customer_reviews.author: Ken Smith

customer_reviews.title: Great for the money.
customer_reviews.text: Well made and sturdy. My 12 string fits perfect. It's a little heavy but nothing to complain about.
customer_reviews.author: Steve Walsingham

customer_reviews.title: Perfect for that 3/4 size guitar that you want to travel with
customer_reviews.text: I boujght my wife the Luna 3/4 for Christmas and when we took our first flight with it I bought her this case. It fit perfectly and protected it well. Good buy.
customer_reviews.author: jaxmandue

customer_reviews.title: Great case
customer_reviews.text: Great case but horrible packing job!! Box arrived with the case almost coming out AND with a scuff mark. Had to keep it as is as I don't have the time to return it and get a new one as I traveling soon.
customer_reviews.author: FJE

customer_reviews.title: Nice case
customer_reviews.text: Nice case. No scratches, dings or anything else. Plush inside and an extra big storage compartment inside compared to other cases I have had.
customer_reviews.author: J

customer_reviews.title: Perfect for OM
customer_reviews.text: Perfect fit for the OM I built from the StewMac kit. Sturdy, "firm" fit, plush interior, latches all worked. I bought one from another dealer- the dimensions said it would fit, but it was described as a classical guitar case. The dimensions were correct, but the "shape" was slightly different and the upper bouts were too tight. This case fit perfectly.
customer_reviews.author: Michael K.

customer_reviews.title: ... bigger than my 3/4 size Luna guitar but fits better than anything else I've found
customer_reviews.text: It's a little bigger than my 3/4 size Luna guitar but fits better than anything else I've found. My guitar seems to be doing okay with a couple old t-shirts stuffed up by the head and the strap in with the body. Not perfect but SIGNIFICANTLY better than anything else I could find
customer_reviews.author: Katrina

customer_reviews.title: Spend the time to measure your guitar
customer_reviews.text: I have a parlor sized guitar, perfect fit and great protection. Would buy again.
customer_reviews.author: NKY Ballplayer

customer_reviews.title: Very nice and sturdy
customer_reviews.text: Very nice and sturdy! Love it. It's light weight and easy to carry. You won't have to worry about damaging your guitar with this case. Worth it for the price. I was afraid that it wasn't going to fit my guitar but it did perfectly. Has a nice little compartment that you canput your picks and miscellaneous items in. My only complaint is that it has too many locks on it, but it's whatever.
customer_reviews.author: Tou Vang

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: Bought it open box it was in absolute perfect shape and real value and very well put together.
customer_reviews.author: Charlie

customer_reviews.title: Excellent Case

customer_reviews.title: the guitar fits like it was made for this case and the case ...
customer_reviews.text: Bought this for my Cordoba Cadete 3/4 sized classical, mostly on the strength of another review on site. As the other guy noted, the guitar fits like it was made for this case and the case itself is of high quality... Hardware appears first-rate...Very nice case for the money.
customer_reviews.author: Mark J. Werner

customer_reviews.title: Excellent case
customer_reviews.text: Excellent product. You seriously could sit on this case and not hurt your guitar (don't do it). Inside liner is very nice. Worth the price. Solid and well-built.
customer_reviews.author: Higgibaby

customer_reviews.title: Another not as pictured or advertised purchase from Amazon
customer_reviews.text: The guitar case is not as advertised and pictured to be " arch topped." I passed on other cases for not having this, that would have been better.
customer_reviews.author: nm156

customer_reviews.title: Returned it for the SKB which was perfect (course it was really made for the BT) If ...
customer_reviews.text: Bought this to protect my Baby Taylor on business trips. Decent fit and finish on the product but just too big and sloppy for my BT. Returned it for the SKB which was perfect (course it was really made for the BT) If you have a 3/4 guitar that is a little larger than the Baby Taylor - this is probably your case.
customer_reviews.author: Bret W. Guthrie

customer_reviews.title: Awesome
customer_reviews.text: Fit my Blueridge 3/4 perfect. Very nice quality will buy another for my full size
customer_reviews.author: BP

customer_reviews.title: Great Case For The Money
customer_reviews.text: This case is a very sturdy case by a brand I've known for quite sometime. At 90 USD I almost chose a cheaper 30 dollar gig bag but I'm very glad I made this purchase. Protected my Acoustic while we drove from Southern California to Oregon and took the heat and morning dew like a champ. 9/10 would recommend to anyone if it was a tad cheaper.
customer_reviews.author: Zoltan Youtz

customer_reviews.title: Fits a mini martin
customer_reviews.text: Just ok. The latches are about as cheap as can be and dont seem to really hold closed very well. Interior is good though a little loose on a mini Martin.
customer_reviews.author: Tyler

customer_reviews.title: Overall a decent case for the price
customer_reviews.text: It’s a bit flimsier than it seems from the pictures and description. I actually had to exchange the first one I ordered since it arrived with about a 1 inch puncture hole on the bottom. (It also seemed used which is a separate issue) The replacement is unscathed and overall seems to be a decent case, especially for the price. I got the 000 size, which fits my Art & Lutherie Legacy Concert Hall perfectly.
customer_reviews.author: EH

customer_reviews.title: 3/4, not classical or parlor
customer_reviews.text: It3 a goog wooden case. Too narrow for classical or parlor sized guitars.

customer_reviews.title: Measure your guitar first.
customer_reviews.text: This is a beautiful, well made guitar case. Unfortunately it's too small for my guitar. I just assumed all clasical guitars were the same size. So it's a good idea to measure your guitar befor you order.
customer_reviews.author: ML

customer_reviews.title: I like the idea of having a hardshell case for my ...
customer_reviews.text: I like the idea of having a hardshell case for my guitars. I was disappointed that it arrived with a small gauge on one side. The case was needed so I settled. I don’t think it was the he fault of the manufacturer but the fulfillment center perhaps.
customer_reviews.author: Keith Greene

customer_reviews.title: My guitar fits great!
customer_reviews.text: I just received my case and my Cordoba guitar fits like a glove. There is a small ding along one edge that has broken through down to the plywood (hence the three stars and not higher), but over all I am pleased with the case. I have not noticed any odor as was mentioned in some of the reviews I read before I purchased the product.
customer_reviews.author: brynphalan

customer_reviews.title: Broken ALREADY?!?!?
customer_reviews.text: I bought this case for my son for Christmas, 2018. The center latch pulled loose from the case as he was closing it yesterday, March 06, 2019. Maybe they should change the name to "Tater".
customer_reviews.author: Gene L. Tannehill

The GWE series guitar cases also come with standard locking latches for extra security.
